      "message": "Can I ask, how is is supposed to be working in the grand scheme of things?\n\nFor example pldm daemon has discovered a SmartNIC which reports via its PLDM PDR 3 Redfish Resources with `\"ContainingResourceID\": 0` (EXTERNAL):\n1)\n```\n\"ProposedContainingResourceName\": \"NetworkAdapterCollection.NetworkAdapterCollection\"\n\"MajorSchemaName\": \"NetworkAdapter.NetworkAdapter\"\n```\n2)\n```\n\"ProposedContainingResourceName\": \"PCIeDeviceCollection.PCIeDeviceCollection\"\n\"MajorSchemaName\": \"PCIeDevice.PCIeDevice\"\n```\n3)\n```\n\"ProposedContainingResourceName\": \"NetworkInterfaceCollection.NetworkInterfaceCollection\"\n\"MajorSchemaName\": \"NetworkInterface.NetworkInterface\"\n```\n\nHow will PLDM daemon know which absolute URLs correspond to these resources?",
      "revId": "c7fa048ac33ae881daf076b521e2f7b19ca88f8f",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
