      "side": 1,
      "message": "By design this is not resolved here in libbej — this patch only\n  performs the DSP0218 Table 42 placeholder \u003c-\u003e value substitution against a\n  caller-supplied BejDeferredBindingMap. Deciding the absolute URLs is the\n  consumer\u0027s (pldmd\u0027s) responsibility, and it is not arbitrary: pldmd follows the\n  Redfish spec, encoded as a static collection-URI table.\n\n  On the pldmd side the flow is:\n\n  1. The Redfish Resource PDRs are parsed into per-resource metadata\n     (resourceId, ProposedContainingResourceName, MajorSchemaName,\n     ContainingResourceID, resource flags).\n  2. pldmd maps each resource to its canonical Redfish collection via a static\n     table derived from the Redfish schema/collection-URI conventions\n     (e.g. NetworkAdapterCollection -\u003e /redfish/v1/Chassis/\u003cns\u003e/NetworkAdapters).\n     It then builds the map entry: uri (for %L\u003cid\u003e), instanceId (for %I\u003cid\u003e),\n     and action targets (for %T\u003cid\u003e.\u003caction\u003e). The final URI is\n     \u003ccollection-prefix\u003e/\u003cinstanceId\u003e.\n  3. That map is passed to decode()/encode().\n\n  For ContainingResourceID \u003d 0 (EXTERNAL), pldmd does not rely on the device\u0027s\n  proposed position; it places the resource under the spec-defined collection\n  keyed by ProposedContainingResourceName / MajorSchemaName. So for your SmartNIC\n  example (tid \u003d T, resourceId \u003d R) these resolve to:\n\n  - NetworkAdapterCollection / NetworkAdapter\n      -\u003e /redfish/v1/Chassis/\u003cns\u003e/NetworkAdapters/\u003cinstanceId\u003e\n  - PCIeDeviceCollection / PCIeDevice\n      -\u003e /redfish/v1/Systems/\u003cns\u003e/PCIeDevices/\u003cinstanceId\u003e\n  - NetworkInterfaceCollection / NetworkInterface\n      -\u003e /redfish/v1/Systems/\u003cns\u003e/NetworkInterfaces/\u003cinstanceId\u003e\n\n  Note: the \u003cns\u003e namespace segment (e.g. \"RDE\") and the \u003cinstanceId\u003e form\n  (e.g. RDE_\u003ctid\u003e_\u003cresourceId\u003e) are pldmd implementation choices and can be\n  changed by the implementation; libbej just substitutes the placeholders with those values.",
